issue.title: Smart Pointers and hints out of order
issue.body:
Maybe this is just how I've been working through the exercises, but I have one shell with `rustlings watch` running and another shell where I type `rustlings hint next` when I want to read the hints.

When I get to the smart pointer exercise, it seems that `rustlings watch` runs the exercises in alphabetical order within each directory, but `rustlings hint next` uses the order defined in `info.toml`. This means that the exercise is `arc1.rs` but the hint is for `box1.rs`. The hint was obviously very confusing. As others have mentioned, the smart pointer section is a bit of a leap already 😄 .
